    "body": "### Rationale\r\n\r\nSpack should at least give a warning (or, better, don't even try) when a package specified as a provider for some virtual package but doesn't provide that package.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWith a large stack (environment) concretization can take infinite time (never completes but doesn't fail with stack overflow or some other error) if a package specified as a provider for some virtual package but doesn't provide that package.\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n<!--*Add any other context about the feature request here.*-->\r\n\r\n\r\n### General information\r\n\r\n- [x] I have run `spack --version` and reported the version of Spack\r\n- [x] I have searched the issues of this repo and believe this is not a duplicate\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ spack --version\r\n0.16.0-1288-ca69e7c\r\n```",
